From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000009 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: local-loongarch64-adaptation <local@example.invalid>
Date: Wed, 24 Jun 2026 10:45:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] crate_universe: add loongarch64 vendored cfg selects

Reason:
0008 makes the checked-in crate_universe vendored crates compatible with the
LoongArch64 platform, but several generated BUILD files also contain
platform-specific select() expressions for dependencies and crate features.

On loongarch64-unknown-linux-gnu these selects must not fall through to their
default empty branch when the corresponding Rust cfg is a generic Unix/Linux
condition. The observed failure in getrandom-0.2.10 is one example: the crate
compiles Unix libc code, but its generated Bazel deps did not select libc for
LoongArch64.

Add loongarch64-unknown-linux-gnu to the generic Unix/Linux/not-windows
vendored select() branches. Do not copy branches whose cfg is explicitly for
other CPU architectures such as aarch64, x86, or x86_64.

diff --git a/crate_universe/3rdparty/crates/BUILD.bitflags-2.4.1.bazel b/crate_universe/3rdparty/crates/BUILD.bitflags-2.4.1.bazel
index 6ceb2d6be..92e2da126 100644
--- a/crate_universe/3rdparty/crates/BUILD.bitflags-2.4.1.bazel
+++ b/crate_universe/3rdparty/crates/BUILD.bitflags-2.4.1.bazel
@@ -47,6 +47,9 @@ rust_library(
         "@rules_rust//rust/platform:aarch64-unknown-linux-gnu": [
             "std",  # aarch64-unknown-linux-gnu
         ],
+        "@rules_rust//rust/platform:loongarch64-unknown-linux-gnu": [
+            "std",  # loongarch64-unknown-linux-gnu
+        ],
         "@rules_rust//rust/platform:aarch64-unknown-nixos-gnu": [
             "std",  # aarch64-unknown-nixos-gnu
         ],
